Teriyaki Salmon
Teriyaki salmon
Preparation time
less than 30 mins
Cooking time
10 to 30 mins
Serves
Serves 2
This teriyaki salmon recipe is on the table in five simple steps. Perfect for a
quick weeknight supper. 
 
This meal provides 524 kcal, 35.5g protein, 39.5g carbohydrate (of which
14.5g sugars), 24.9g fat (of which 4.5g saturates), 1.4g fibre and 5.8g salt per
portion.
By Mike Robinson
From Saturday Kitchen
Ingredients
2 salmon fillets
4-5 tbsp dark soy sauce
1 lime, zest and juice
1 small chilli
2 tbsp maple syrup
1 fat garlic clove, finely chopped
1 chunk of ginger, finely chopped
1 sheet of egg noodles
bunch of coriander, chopped
